<h2>What Makes a Great Developer Tool?</h2>

<p>
  After building and curating dozens of developer tools, here's what separates great tools from mediocre ones:
</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Speed</strong> — The tool should respond instantly. No loading spinners, no server round-trips for basic operations.</li>
  <li><strong>Privacy</strong> — Data should be processed in the browser whenever possible. Your API keys, tokens, and code should never leave your machine.</li>
  <li><strong>No signup</strong> — Developer tools should work immediately. Registration walls for basic utilities are a dealbreaker.</li>
  <li><strong>Mobile-friendly</strong> — You will debug things from your phone at some point. The tool should work on mobile.</li>
  <li><strong>Dark mode</strong> — Developers live in dark mode. If a tool burns your retinas at midnight, it's not a developer tool.</li>
</ul>

